{
  "id": "variable-font-weight",
  "title": "Interactive Variable Weight",
  "summary": "Headline letters thicken toward the cursor — each glyph's weight responds to how close the pointer is, like a spotlight of boldness.",
  "description": "Variable-font interactivity is a 2026 typography trend. Each letter is a span; on pointermove, its font-weight (font-variation-settings 'wght') is set by its distance to the cursor, so a wave of weight follows the pointer across the word. Smoothly interpolates with a true variable font.",
