  "browser_support": "Variable fonts everywhere; smoothest with a loaded variable font. With static system fonts it snaps between available weights (still effective).",
  "performance_notes": "One pointermove writing font-variation-settings on each letter span. Fine for headline-length text; avoid on whole paragraphs.",
  "accessibility_notes": "The full word stays as text (and as the heading's accessible name); weight is decorative. Pointer-only; disabled under prefers-reduced-motion.",
